Box 68, 108 West Stuart Drive, Galax, VA 24333 Office Hours are 8:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m., Monday through Friday, 20870=The investigation of an infant who died July 16 is continuing by the Grayson County Sheriff’s Department. Sheriff Richard Vaughan said an autopsy was performed on 1-month-old Caidance Adare Skoski at the State Medical Examiner’s Office in Roanoke but no report had been received. “It will probably take several weeks to get all the test results back so we can determine the cause of death,” Vaughan said. He also said they were awaiting the results of toxicology and other tests.
